{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"626070f8-2252-4edb-bdd2-e4d7d438c5af","content":"No repo files to inspect, so here's the migration guidance directly.\n\n## Migrating from `VSTest@3` to Microsoft.Testing.Platform\n\n### 1. Update your test projects\n\nIn each test `.csproj`, add:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nFor TRX reports, add the NuGet package:\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n```\n\nFor code coverage, add:\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CodeCoverage\" Version=\"1.*\" />\n```\n\n### 2. Replace `VSTest@3` in your pipeline\n\n**Before (VSTest@3):**\n```yaml\n- task: VSTest@3\n  inputs:\n    testSelector: 'testAssemblies'\n    testAssemblyVer2: '**\\*Tests.dll'\n    codeCoverageEnabled: true\n```\n\n**After (`dotnet test`):**\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run Tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: 'test'\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >-\n      --configuration Release\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      -- \n      --report-trx\n      --report-trx-filename TestResults.trx\n      --coverage\n      --coverage-output-format cobertura\n      --coverage-output $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/coverage.cobertura.xml\n```\n\n### 3. Publish results & coverage\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish TRX Results'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: 'VSTest'\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish Code Coverage'\n  condition: always()\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/coverage.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n### Key differences\n\n| Concern | VSTest@3 | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Test runner | vstest.console | Built into the test executable |\n| Invocation | Matches DLLs | `dotnet test` on `.csproj` |\n| TRX reports | Built-in | `--report-trx` (via NuGet extension) |\n| Code coverage | `codeCoverageEnabled` | `--coverage` (via NuGet extension) |\n| Result publishing | Automatic | Explicit `PublishTestResults@2` step |\n\nThe `--` separator before `--report-trx` and `--coverage` is required — arguments after `--` are passed to the testing platform, not to `dotnet test`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c4434132-b6f4-470b-ac40-74cb5a2f3eae","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty - no existing pipeline files to look at. This is a general guidance question. Let me provide a concise answer about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform while keeping TRX and code coverage.","outputTokens":800,"requestId":"A02F:1FF93E:C0B3A3:E15130:69FE8604"},"id":"bae5f92d-1732-4777-adac-01a4cd4bfada","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:55:48.624Z","parentId":"e0a616b8-eb63-48a0-b1e4-a0af19d8a25a"}
